owAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1134.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Forming Mage Group</span><hr size=1> I'm up for this myself. Currently grinding through 40 in Dawnshroud, as wolf adds allow.<br><br>How is Kaesora solo?<br><br><br>Goedel<br>Magician of Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uurzah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Urzah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/13/02 9:55:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1134.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Forming Mage Group</span><hr size=1> I do ok though I'm not an uber mage by any stretch of the imagination.  Kaesora is cool in that there is an 18% exp bonus but Some days I have trouble.  Right now my mage is  43 using a 39 pet, so it can be challenging.<br><br>I use the gate method to break spawns.  Send a fireshielded earth pet in to a room with multiple spawns and burn down his current target as fast as I can.  Gate as soon as i see the exp message and then med up for a repeat on the remaining.  This works 90% of the time for me.  It has the added benifit of being a bit exciting - for me that is cool because I hate being bored.  <br><br>If i get bored I find other things to do and that means I don't level - hehe<br><br>In any case I was reading on how awesome and fun an all mage group could be and wanted to try it.  Fun is what this game is supposed to be about. <p><br><img src=http://www.virtual-empires.com/sigs/UrzahTxt.gif><br><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68942>My Maglo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub9